<knowledge>
	<title>Diagnosing Diabetes</title>
	<description>This system assesses the risk of people having diabetes and also
   presents the user with lifestyle improvements to lower the risk of diabetes and
   to help people to live a healthier life.</description>

  <!-- First the different types of lifestyle advices as seperate goals, after which follow the diabetes diagnoses goals-->
  <goal name="AdviceSport">
 	<description>Lifestyle Advice: Sport</description>
      	<!-- Based on the answers to the lifestyle questions, we offer specific advice to users. There are many different answer values, as there are many different forms of advice-->
      	<!-- MAYBE SPLIT EACH FORM OF ADVICE IN SEPERATE GOALS??? -->
	 	<answer value="SportMore">You could improve your lifestyle by increasing the amount of exercise you do.</answer>
	    <answer value="no">Your answer seem to indicate that you have a perfect lifestyle concerning sport! Keep up the good work!</answer>
  </goal>

  <goal name="AdviceFood">
 	<description>Lifestyle Advice: Food</description>
      	<!-- Based on the answers to the lifestyle questions, we offer specific advice to users. There are many different answer values, as there are many different forms of advice-->
      	<!-- MAYBE SPLIT EACH FORM OF ADVICE IN SEPERATE GOALS??? -->
	 	<answer value="EatMoreVeggiesAndLessSugar">You could improve your eating habits by adding more vegatables to your diet. The Dutch Institute for Food advices to eat at least 250 gram of vegatables each day.
	 	It is also be better to lower your intake of sugar. Food sources that contain a lot of sugar are for example soft drinks, juices, candy, cookies and many types of processed foods. Try to check the amount of sugar on the products that you regularly buy and use this website .. to search for alternative food sources that contain less sugar.
	 	</answer>
	    <answer value="EatMoreVegatables">You could improve your eating habits by adding more vegatables to your diet. The Dutch Institute for Food advices to eat at least 250 gram of vegatables each day.</answer>
	    <answer value="EatLessSugar">It would be better to lower your intake of sugar. Food sources that contain a lot of sugar are for example soft drinks, juices, candy, cookies and many types of processed foods. Try to check the amount of sugar on the products that you regularly buy and use this website .. to search for alternative food sources that contain less sugar.</answer>
	    <answer value="no">Your answer seem to indicate that you have a perfect lifestyle concerning food! Keep up the good work!</answer>
  </goal>

  <goal name="AdviceSmoking">
 	<description>Lifestyle Advice: Smoking</description>
      	<!-- Based on the answers to the lifestyle questions, we offer specific advice to users. There are many different answer values, as there are many different forms of advice-->
      	<!-- MAYBE SPLIT EACH FORM OF ADVICE IN SEPERATE GOALS??? -->
	 	<answer value="QuitSmoking">Smoking can cause all types of disaeases and is heavility related to the risk of forming diabates. We advice you to try and stop smoking, this website contians a lot of useful tips to help you quit: https://www.lung.org/quit-smoking/i-want-to-quit.</answer>
	    <answer value="no">Smoking can cause all types of disaeases, it is therefore great that you do not smoke. Keep it up!</answer>
  </goal>

  <!-- more lifestyle columns will be added here -->

  <goal name="RiskDiabetesType2">
 	<description>Diabetes type 2 risk</description>
        <!-- These are the goal values of diagnosing diabetes type 2. There are 3 risk assessment values, as adviced by our expert.  -->
        <answer value="lowRisk2">You have a low risk of having diabetes type 2. </answer>
        <answer value="mediumRisk2">You have a medium risk of having diabetes type 2. We advice you to visit a doctor to take a diabetes test. A simple blood test at your general practitioner can quickly confirm this. It will be especially valuable to follow the lifestyle tips that the systems gives, as a good and healthy lifestyle can help to decrease the risk of forming diabetes type 2 and can also improve your life if you suffer from diabetes.
        </answer>
        <answer value="highRisk2">You have a high risk of having diabetes type 1. We advice you to visit a doctor to take a diabetes test. A simple blood test at your general practitioner can quickly confirm this. It will be especially valuable to follow the lifestyle tips that the systems gives, as a good and healthy lifestyle can help to decrease the risk of forming diabetes type 2 and can also improve your life if you suffer from diabetes.
        </answer>
        <answer value="no"></answer>
  </goal>

<!-- As adviced by our expert, we first assess the risk of having diabetes type 1, as in that case, many diabetes type 2 and lifestyle related questions are unneccesary to ask. -->
  <goal name="RiskDiabetesType1">
 	<description>Diabetes Type 1 risk</description>
      	<!-- There are 2 possible forms of diabetes that can occur in our test. Here are first the possibilities of answers for a risk assesment of diabetes type 1. No lifestyle advice is given here, as that does not apply to people with (a risk of) diabetes 1. -->
	    <answer value="mediumRisk1">You have a medium risk of having diabetes type 1. We advice you to visit a doctor to take a diabetes test. A simple blood test at your general practitioner can quickly confirm this. </answer>
	    <answer value="highRisk1">You have a high risk of having diabetes type 1. We advice you to visit a doctor and take a diabetes test. A simple blood test at your general practitioner can quickly confirm this.</answer>
	    <answer value="ketoacidose">You are experiencing the symptoms of a ketoacidose, this an advanced and dangerous stage of diabetes type 1. We advice you to go to call a doctor as soon as possible or possibly call the emergency services. </answer>
        <!-- It could also be that a person does not have diabetes type 1 symptoms, but the symptoms relate to some other disease, our test is incapalbe of assesssing these other possible diseases as our expert lacks knowledge about this -->
        <answer value="OtherSymptoms">Your symptoms seem not to be related to diabetes, we do advice you to see a doctor.</answer>

        <answer value="No"></answer>
  </goal>


